The paper deals with facial expression recognition using deep learning techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training the model using large datasets, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques for recognizing emotions, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the human-computer interaction aspect of recognizing emotions, which falls under the sub-category cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper involves the use of image processing techniques, which falls under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
